5Ô∏è‚É£ Edge Cases & Considerations
6Ô∏è‚É£ Conclusion

Payroll cancellation can be initiated by the employer via UI or triggered by risk-related events.
The cancellation workflow depends on when the request is received:

Scenario,System Response
Same-day payroll cancellation,Determines if processing is in progress and either halts or rolls back.
Future-dated payroll cancellation,Cancels before execution and removes event from EventBridge & ACH Risk Processing.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Employer initiates payroll cancellation  
2Ô∏è‚É£ Determine processing step (SafePay, ACH, etc.)  
3Ô∏è‚É£ Decision: Halt processing or wait until completion  
4Ô∏è‚É£ If SafePay initiated ‚Üí Send PATCH request to cancel  
5Ô∏è‚É£ If ACH initiated ‚Üí Request ACH cancellation before cutoff  
6Ô∏è‚É£ Final status update & employer notified  

Decision Points

‚úÖ Processing Not Started ‚Üí Payroll is canceled immediately.
‚úÖ Processing Started (Before SafePay) ‚Üí Halt execution, rollback steps.
‚úÖ SafePay Processed But ACH Not Yet ‚Üí Send PATCH request to SafePay.
‚úÖ ACH Processed ‚Üí ACH cancellation depends on cutoff time.

üîπ Decision Points

‚úÖ Processing Not Started ‚Üí Payroll is canceled immediately.
‚úÖ Processing Started (Before SafePay) ‚Üí Halt execution, rollback steps.
‚úÖ SafePay Processed But ACH Not Yet ‚Üí Send PATCH request to SafePay.
‚úÖ ACH Processed ‚Üí ACH cancellation depends on cutoff time.

üîπ Detailed Steps

1Ô∏è‚É£ Employer requests cancellation in UI.
2Ô∏è‚É£ System checks if processing has started.
3Ô∏è‚É£ If not started, remove payroll from queue & notify employer.
4Ô∏è‚É£ If processing has started:
	‚Ä¢	Before SafePay: Halt processing.
	‚Ä¢	After SafePay Authorization: Use SafePay PATCH API to cancel.
	‚Ä¢	After ACH Submission: ACH may allow cancellation if before 8 PM EST cutoff.
5Ô∏è‚É£ Notify employer of cancellation status.

Future-Dated Payroll Cancellation
1Ô∏è‚É£ Employer requests cancellation before payroll execution date  
2Ô∏è‚É£ Check if ACH risk evaluation was already performed  
3Ô∏è‚É£ If ACH risk evaluation occurred ‚Üí Notify ACH to cancel risk evaluation  
4Ô∏è‚É£ Remove payroll event from EventBridge scheduler  
5Ô∏è‚É£ Notify employer that cancellation is successful  

üîπ Decision Points

‚úÖ If payroll is not yet scheduled, remove from EventBridge & database.
‚úÖ If ACH risk check was already performed, send ACH cancellation request.
‚úÖ If SafePay & ACH were not triggered, payroll is canceled without issue.

üîπ Detailed Steps

1Ô∏è‚É£ Employer requests future-dated payroll cancellation.
2Ô∏è‚É£ System checks if ACH risk evaluation has occurred:
	‚Ä¢	YES ‚Üí Send a cancel request to ACH.
	‚Ä¢	NO ‚Üí Remove event from database & EventBridge.
3Ô∏è‚É£ Notify employer that payroll has been canceled successfully.

Decision Points ‚Äì In-Flight Cancellation vs. Waiting
Scenario,System Response
Payroll has not yet started processing,Cancellation is immediate, removed from all queues.
Payroll is in SafePay Authorization,SafePay PATCH API cancels the transaction.
Payroll has reached ACH Processing,If before 8 PM cutoff, ACH cancellation may be possible.
ACH processing completed,Payroll cannot be canceled. Employer notified.
Payroll is scheduled in EventBridge,Remove event from EventBridge scheduler.

Scenario,System Response
Employer cancels after ACH cutoff (8 PM EST),ACH processing cannot be canceled. Employer notified.
Employer cancels payroll after SafePay approval,Use SafePay PATCH API to cancel.
Employer updates payroll before execution date,Old payroll is canceled, and new payroll is scheduled.
Duplicate cancellation requests received,Deduplication logic prevents unnecessary SafePay/ACH calls.





